---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import mee from '../images/mee.jpg';
import sculpture from '../images/sculpture.jpg';
---

<Layout title="About — Narmeen Zain" description="About Narmeen Zain — award-winning, internationally exhibited artist">
  <div class="container mx-auto p-3 md:p-1 fadeInUp">

    <!-- portrait + bio -->
    <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-3 pb-20">
      <div class="md:col-span-1 flex flex-col items-center justify-center">
        <Image src={mee} alt="Artist portrait" class="rounded-full h-48 w-48 object-cover -scale-x-100 hover:animate-pulse" />
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-2 md:col-start-2 lg:pr-12">
        <p class="py-2 text-2xl text-gray-600 font-bold">Hii</p>
        <p class="pr-4">I'm an award-winning, internationally exhibited artist. I've been exhibiting since 2011 and
        mostly paint with oils and acrylics but sometimes create mixed media pieces with embroidery or knit work.
        I also very occasionally sculpt with ceramic clay.</p>
        <p class="p-1">Outside of art, I'm a computer scientist and classically trained pianist.</p>

        <div class="pt-7 w-3/4 xl:w-1/5">
          <a href="mailto:nszain@pm.me"
            class="bg-green-900 hover:bg-green-800 shadow-md hover:shadow-xl text-white font-semibold py-3 px-5 rounded-3xl grid grid-flow-col-dense hover:-translate-y-1 transition-transform"
            id="mailcheck">
            <div id="mailimg"></div>
            <p class="font-medium text-lg">Say hello!</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- sculpture image -->
    <Image src={sculpture} alt="Sculpture of a human head" class="rounded w-full fadeInUp" />

    <!-- gallery representation -->
    <div class="my-12 h-px border-t-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-gray-400 via-gray-700 to-transparent opacity-50"></div>
    <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-5">
      <div class="md:col-span-2">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 font-bold p-2">GALLERY REPRESENTATION</p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-1 md:col-start-3 flex flex-col items-center justify-center">
        <p class="pb-1 text-xl font-bold text-lime-900">DIAC</p>
        <p class="p-1 text-base">Dubai, UAE</p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-1 md:col-start-4 flex flex-col items-center justify-center">
        <p class="pb-1 text-xl font-bold text-lime-900">ISOAG</p>
        <p class="p-1 text-base">Dubai, UAE</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- about the art + artist statement -->
    <div class="my-8 h-px border-t-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-gray-400 via-gray-700 to-transparent opacity-50"></div>
    <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="md:p-1 md:col-span-1">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 font-bold p-3 underline decoration-double decoration-lime-600">ABOUT THE ART</p>
        <p class="p-1 pr-3">I started learning to paint with acrylics but ended up gravitating towards oils for the depth and richness of colour.
        These days, I'm experimenting more with mixed media and sculpture.</p>
        <p class="p-1 pr-3">Above all, I value connection and emotion in my work.
        The viewer, then, becomes vital. I am looking for acceptance and reciprocity and connection. The message doesn't exist unless it's in
        the act of being perceived.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-1">
        <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-10">
          <div class="md:col-span-1 md:h-[250px] md:min-h-[1em] md:w-px md:self-stretch bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent via-gray-700 to-transparent opacity-40"></div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 font-bold p-3 underline decoration-2 decoration-lime-600">ARTIST STATEMENT</p>
            <p class="p-1 pr-5">I think people, places, objects, are only as obedient to their outlines as we expect them to be. There's a volatility there that I sometimes forget. Objects don't exist in isolation.
            The links between them are hard for me to put into words but I know that we overlap more than we are separate. When I look into a mirror my face is broken into billions of others. My work relies on this enmeshment.</p>
            <p class="p-1 pr-5">I have said before that many of my paintings begin in dreams. I am using paint and thread now to show them to you. There is something to be said that exists outside the bounds of language. I've said it as best I can.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- exhibitions -->
    <div class="my-12 h-px border-t-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-gray-400 via-gray-700 to-transparent opacity-50"></div>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 font-bold p-1 pb-4">SELECTED EXHIBITIONS</p>
    <p class="p-1">2024 <b><i>Emozion</i></b>, Gadarte Associazione Culturale, Florence, Italy</p>
    <p class="p-1">2024 <b><i>Telavi History Museum</i></b>, Telavi, Georgia</p>
    <p class="p-1">2023 <b><i>ISOAG Annual Art Exhibition</i></b>, Dubai, UAE</p>
    <p class="p-1">2023 <b><i>One World One Earth</i></b>, Taj Mahal Palace Hotel, Mumbai, India</p>
    <p class="p-1">2023 <b><i>Annual Exhibition</i></b>, Rukseen Art Gallery, Dubai, United Arab Emirates</p>
    <p class="p-1">2023 <b><i>Vasudhaiv Kutumbakam</i></b>, Indian Embassy, Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates</p>
    <p class="p-1">2023 <b><i>A Journey Through Creativity</i></b>, Hotel H, Dubai, United Arab Emirates</p>
    <p class="p-1">2012–2014 Permanently exhibited, ArtChowk — the Gallery, Karachi, Pakistan</p>
    <p class="p-1">2014 <b><i>Students' Exhibition</i></b>, Gallery 76, Dubai, United Arab Emirates</p>

    <!-- press -->
    <div class="my-12 h-px border-t-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-gray-400 via-gray-700 to-transparent opacity-50"></div>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 font-bold p-1 pb-4">SELECTED PRESS</p>
    <p class="p-1">2024 <b>Canvas of Artist Memories</b> Autobiography Coffee Table Book, published by Namaste India Magazine</p>
    <p class="p-1">2023 <b>Gulf Today</b>, <i>"<a class="underline decoration-2 decoration-orange-600 hover:no-underline hover:text-orange-900 font-semibold" href="https://www.gulftoday.ae/culture/2023/09/21/the-art-of-dreams-computer-scientist-narmeen-zain-teams-with-dreams-for-art">The Art of Dreams: Computer scientist Narmeen Zain teams with dreams for art</a>"</i></p>

    <!-- distinctions -->
    <div class="my-12 h-px border-t-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-gray-400 via-gray-700 to-transparent opacity-50"></div>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 font-bold p-1 pb-4">DISTINCTIONS</p>
    <p class="p-1">2013 <b>Juror's Choice</b>, Gallery 72</p>
    <p class="p-1 pb-16">2011 <b>First Place</b>, Gallery 72</p>

  </div>
</Layout>
